item.title: Project 1: Google Play Store 2018 EDA
item.description: Background Google Play Store consists of numerous applications within varying categories. As a digital distribution service for Android, users have access to a number of family, gaming, and tool apps, to name a few. There were approximately 2.7 million applications available as of February 2017. The scraped Kaggle data reveals a sample of the Google Play Store as of 2018. The dataset reveals 33 categories in the Google Play Store.
